<subSubSection id="C372B1CA2E23FFA1FF068899FC0FF8A2" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD7E2412E23FFA1FF068899FBB0FAC2" blockId="2.[166,1225,990,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">General. Relatively small acanthocephalans. Trunk with discoid widening and two fields of spines in anterior part. Anterior field of spines broadest on ventral surface, narrow dorsally. Posterior field of spines broadest ventrally. Maximum width of bare zone between fields of spines 150. In anterior field of spines, length of spines decreasing from apical (38– 49), to basal (29–31). In posterior field of spines, length of spines increasing from apical (32–37) to median (39–41) and decreasing posteriorly (28). Ventral spines almost reaching posterior end of trunk. Genital spines absent. Proboscis almost cylindrical, with dilatation in posterior third, with 18 longitudinal rows of 11 hooks in each. First 7 hooks large, with strong roots directed posteriorly. Next 4 hooks spiniform, without roots. Proboscis receptacle double-walled, with cerebral ganglion in its anterior third. Neck distinct. Lemnisci sacciform, attached in neck, not reaching level of proboscis receptacle bottom.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7E2412E23FFA1FF068E39FB8DF902" blockId="2.[166,1225,990,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FEB18E39FD48FAE3" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Yamaguti" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[364,708,1374,1400]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Andracantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="phalacrocoracis">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FEB18E39FD48FAE3" box="[364,708,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Andracantha phalacrocoracis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common parasite of fish-eating birds. It was initially described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FDDD8E19FD45FA02" author="Yamaguti, S." box="[512,713,1406,1433]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" pagination="317 - 351" refId="ref8840" refString="Yamaguti, S. 1939. Studies on the helminth fauna of Japan, part 29. Acanthocephala, II. Japanese Journal Zoo 1 ogy, 8, 317 - 351." type="journal article" year="1939">Yamaguti (1939)</bibRefCitation>
from pelagic cormorants (
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FBCF8E19FB44FA03" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Yamaguti" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[1042,1224,1406,1432]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Andracantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="phalacrocoracis">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FBCF8E19FB44FA03" box="[1042,1224,1406,1432]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Phalacrocoracis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FF7B8EF9FED1FA22" authority="Pallas" authorityName="Pallas" box="[166,349,1438,1465]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Profilicollis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="pelagicus">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FF7B8EF9FE83FA23" box="[166,271,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">pelagicus</emphasis>
Pallas
</taxonomicName>
) from Shikoku Islands, 
<collectingCountry id="F37FA2D12E23FFA1FDA08EF9FD4FFA22" box="[637,707,1438,1465]" name="Japan" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Japan</collectingCountry>
. This species was also reported from blacklegged kittiwakes 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FEA48ED8FD34FA42" authority="(Linnaeus)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[377,696,1470,1497]" class="Aves" family="Laridae" genus="Rissa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tridactyla">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FEA48ED8FDA2FA43" box="[377,558,1470,1496]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Rissa tridactyla</emphasis>
(Linnaeus)
</taxonomicName>
, slaty-backed gull (
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FC438ED8FF43FA62" authority="Steineger" authorityName="Steineger" class="Aves" family="Laridae" genus="Larus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schistisagus">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FC438ED8FBE2FA43" box="[926,1134,1470,1496]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Larus schistisagus</emphasis>
Steineger
</taxonomicName>
), black-throated loon (
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FE078EB9FD66FA62" authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" box="[474,746,1502,1529]" class="Aves" family="Gaviidae" genus="Gavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gaviiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arctica">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FE078EB9FDF9FA63" box="[474,629,1502,1528]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Gavia arctica</emphasis>
Linnaeus
</taxonomicName>
), hooded crow 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FC418EB9FB48FA62" authority="(Linnaeus)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[924,1220,1502,1529]" class="Aves" family="Corvidae" genus="Corvus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cornix">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FC418EB9FBB0FA63" box="[924,1084,1502,1528]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Corvus cornix</emphasis>
(Linnaeus)
</taxonomicName>
, carrion crow 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FE988E99FDFEF982" authority="(Linnaeus)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[325,626,1534,1561]" class="Aves" family="Corvidae" genus="Corvus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="corone">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FE988E99FE60F983" box="[325,492,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Corvus corone</emphasis>
(Linnaeus)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FD738E98FCB9F983" box="[686,821,1534,1560]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Profilicollis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="pelagicus">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FD738E98FCB9F983" box="[686,821,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">P. pelagicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Far East from 
<collectingRegion id="49AC2CA32E23FFA1FB898E99FB45F982" box="[1108,1225,1534,1561]" country="Russia" name="Chukotka" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Chukotka</collectingRegion>
to the Prymorye, 
<collectingCountry id="F37FA2D12E23FFA1FEA18D79FE44F9A2" box="[380,456,1566,1593]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FE078D79FD26F9A2" author="Khokhlova, I. G." box="[474,682,1566,1593]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" pagination="1 - 275" refId="ref7061" refString="Khokhlova, I. G. 1986. Acanthocephala of terrestrial vertebrates of the USSR. Nauka, Moscow, 1 - 275 [In Russian.]" type="book chapter" year="1986">Khokhlova, 1986</bibRefCitation>
), from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FCD88D78FC03F9A3" box="[773,911,1566,1592]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Profilicollis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="pelagicus">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FCD88D78FC03F9A3" box="[773,911,1566,1592]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">P. pelagicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and bald eagles (
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FBB88D79FDA5F9C2" authority="Linnaeus, 1766" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1766" class="Aves" family="Accipitridae" genus="Haliaeetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Accipitriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucocephalus">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FBB88D79FEE3F9C3" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Haliaeetus leucocephalus</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 1766
</taxonomicName>
) from Alaska (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FD048D59FC0AF9C2" author="Schmidt, G. D." box="[729,902,1598,1625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" pagination="615 - 620" refId="ref8351" refString="Schmidt, G. D. 1975. Andracantha, a new genus of Acanthocephala (Polymorphidae) from fish-eating birds with descriptions of three species. Journal of Parasitology, 61 (4), 615 - 620." type="journal article" year="1975">Schmidt, 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FC4C8D59FB37F9C2" author="Richardson, D. J. &amp; Cole, R. A." box="[913,1211,1598,1625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" pagination="540 - 541" refId="ref8106" refString="Richardson, D. J., Cole, R. A. 1997. Acanthocephala of the bald eagle (Haliaeetus leucocephalus) in North America. Journal of Parasitology, 83 (3), 540 - 541." type="journal article" year="1997">Richardson &amp; Cole, 1997</bibRefCitation>
), from the great cormorant 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FE098D39FCFCF9E2" authority="(Blumenbach)" baseAuthorityName="Blumenbach" box="[468,880,1630,1657]" class="Aves" family="Phalacrocoracidae" genus="Phalacrocorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suliformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="carbo">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FE098D39FD4DF9E3" box="[468,705,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Phalacrocorax carbo</emphasis>
(Blumenbach)
</taxonomicName>
from South Moravia, 
<collectingCountry id="F37FA2D12E23FFA1FBB28D39FB49F9E2" box="[1135,1221,1630,1657]" name="Poland" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Poland</collectingCountry>
, on their seasonal migrations (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FDDF8D19FD45F902" author="Okulewicz, A." box="[514,713,1662,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" pagination="19 - 24" refId="ref7953" refString="Okulewicz, A. 2014. Helminths in migrating and wintering birds recorded in Poland. Annals of Parasitology, 60 (1), 19 - 24." type="journal article" year="2014">Okulewicz, 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FD098D19FC79F902" author="Moravec, F. &amp; Scholz, T." box="[724,1013,1662,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" refId="ref7779" refString="Moravec, F., Scholz, T. 2016. Helminth parasites of the lesser great cormorant Phalacrocorax carbo sinensis from two nesting regions in the Czech Republic. Folia Parasitologica, 63, 022." type="book" year="2016">Moravec &amp; Scholz, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7E2412E23FFA1FF068DF9FC0FF8A2" blockId="2.[166,1225,990,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">
Intermediate hosts for 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FE268DF9FD5AF923" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Yamaguti" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[507,726,1694,1720]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Andracantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="phalacrocoracis">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FE268DF9FD5AF923" box="[507,726,1694,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">A. phalacrocoracis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unknown. However, several species from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FEB18DD9FD8BF943" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1975" box="[364,519,1726,1752]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Andracantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91C3E532E23FFA1FEB18DD9FD8BF943" box="[364,519,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Andracantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known to use amphipods as their intermediate hosts (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FF738DB9FE11F962" author="Atrashkevich, G. I." box="[174,413,1758,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" pagination="38 - 42" refId="ref6119" refString="Atrashkevich, G. I. 2008. Spiny-headed worms genus of Corynosoma Luhe, 1904 (Acanthocephala: Polymorphidae) in the Okhotsk sea and parasitic system with dominant species of C. strumosum (Rudolphi, 1819). In: Proceedings of the IV Congress of the Russian Society of Parasitologists, Russian Academy of Sciences, 20 - 25, October, 2008, Zoological Institute RAS, St. Petersburg &quot; Parasitology in XXI century - problems, methods, solutions &quot;, 1, 38 - 42 [In Russian.]" type="journal article" year="2008">Atrashkevich, 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Fishes from three families, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FCD78DB9FC3BF962" box="[778,951,1758,1785]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nototheniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Nototheniidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FC158DB9FB1CF962" box="[968,1168,1758,1785]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bathydraconidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Bathydraconidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6899C22E23FFA1FF7B8D99FEFFF882" authorityName="T.N.Gill" authorityYear="1861" box="[166,371,1790,1817]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Channichthyidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Channichthyidae</taxonomicName>
, were reported as the paratenic hosts for these acanthocephalans (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FBAA8D99FF6DF8A2" author="Rocka, A." pageId="2" pageNumber="183" pagination="26 - 35" refId="ref8201" refString="Rocka, A. 2006. Helminths of Antarctic fishes: life cycle biology, specificity and geographical distribution. Acta Parasitologica, 51, 26 - 35." type="journal article" year="2006">Rocka, 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FF318C79FE60F8A2" author="Laskowski, Z. &amp; Jezewski, W. &amp; Zdzitowiecki, K." box="[236,492,1822,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" pagination="107 - 117" refId="ref7294" refString="Laskowski, Z., Jezewski, W., Zdzitowiecki, K. 2008. Cystacanths of Acanthocephala in notothenioid fish from the Beagle Channel (sub-Antarctica). Systematic Parasitology, 70, 107 - 117." type="journal article" year="2008">Laskowski et al., 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF99FB02E23FFA1FE2A8C79FCFAF8A2" author="Laskowski, Z. &amp; Zdzitowiecki, K." box="[503,886,1822,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" pagination="179 - 186" refId="ref7333" refString="Laskowski, Z., Zdzitowiecki, K. 2009. Occurrence of acanthocephalans in notothenioid fishes in the Beagle Channel (Magellanic sub-region, sub-Antarctic). Polish Polar Research, 30, 179 - 186." type="journal article" year="2009">Laskowski &amp; Zdzitowiecki, 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
